'''Kokuryō Minazuki Festival''' (国領水無月祭) is a {{ill|riverside festival|ja|川裾祭}} held annually on {{ill|July 31|ja|7月31日}} in the Kokuryō district of {{ill|Kasuga, Hyōgo|ja|春日町 (兵庫県)}}, {{ill|Tamba, Hyōgo|ja|丹波市}}, Japan. The festival has continued since the mid-{{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}}.<ref>{{Cite web|ja|url=http://kitakinki.gr.jp/publictopics/5675|title=国領水無月祭|publisher=北近畿広域観光連盟|accessdate=2019-06-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|ja|url=https://www.city.tamba.lg.jp/uploaded/attachment/38717.pdf|title=国領地区自治協議会だより|format=PDF|publisher=国領地区自治協議会|accessdate=2019-06-27}}</ref>== Overview ==The festival is a traditional event that has been held for over 250 years around the {{ill|Takeda River (Hyōgo and Kyoto)|ja|竹田川 (兵庫県・京都府)}} in the Kokuryō district of Kasuga, Tamba City. In the past, summer often brought outbreaks of epidemics. In an era without advanced medical treatments, people gathered by the riverside to worship the gods and purify themselves through ritual cleansing.Since the festival coincided with the midpoint of the year according to the {{ill|lunar calendar|ja|太陰暦}}, people expressed gratitude for the past six months and prayed for good health in the remaining half of the year by receiving amulets and participating in purification rituals.== Events ==* 4:00 PM: Distribution of longevity amulets at the Minazuki Festival altar on Pilgrimage Bridge* 6:00 PM: Shooting gallery* 7:00 PM: {{ill|Lantern Floating|ja|万灯流し}} on the Takeda River (Pilgrimage Bridge)* 7:00 PM & 8:30 PM: Street dance performances* 7:30 PM: Performance by Konchan Band  *(Based on the 2015 schedule)*== Access ==* '''By Train:'''  : From {{ill|Kuroi Station (Hyōgo)|ja|黒井駅 (兵庫県)}} on JR, take the Nosé-bound bus and get off at "Shinshūkō-mae."* '''By Car:'''  : About 8 minutes from {{ill|Kasuga Interchange|ja|春日インターチェンジ}} on the {{ill|Maizuru-Wakasa Expressway|ja|舞鶴若狭自動車道}}.== Organizers ==* Kokuryō Residents’ Association & Kokuryō Minazuki Festival Executive Committee=== Sponsors ===* Kasuga Branch, Tamba City Chamber of Commerce* Kokuryō Shopping District== Gallery ==<gallery widths="180" heights="120">2015-07-31Minazuki-Festival Kokuryo,Tamba,Hyogo-Japan 国領水無月祭り 8564.JPG|People heading to the festival2015-07-31Minazuki-Festival Kokuryo,Tamba,Hyogo-Japan 国領水無月祭り 8726.JPG|Lantern floating on the Takeda River2015-07-31Minazuki-Festival Kokuryo,Tamba,Hyogo-Japan 国領水無月祭り 8597.JPG|Town center2015-07-31Minazuki-Festival Kokuryo,Tamba,Hyogo-Japan 国領水無月祭り 8620.JPG|Town center2015-07-31Minazuki-Festival Kokuryo,Tamba,Hyogo-Japan 国領水無月祭り 8635.JPG|Festival venue center2015-07-31Minazuki-Festival Kokuryo,Tamba,Hyogo-Japan 国領水無月祭り 8659.JPG|Outskirts of town2015-07-31Minazuki-Festival Kokuryo,Tamba,Hyogo-Japan 国領水無月祭り 8580.JPG|Kokuryō River, a tributary</gallery>== References =={{Reflist}}== See Also =={{Commonscat|Kokuryō Minazuki Matsuri}}* {{ill|Riverside festival|ja|川裾祭}}* {{ill|Ayabe Minazuki Festival|ja|あやべ水無月まつり}}* {{ill|Atago Festival (Tamba)|ja|愛宕祭 (丹波市)}}{{DEFAULTSORT:Kokuryō Minazuki Matsuri}}]][[Category:Festivals in Hyōgo Prefecture]]]][[ja:]][[Category:Fireworks festivals in Hyōgo Prefecture]]]][[ja:]][[Category:History of Tamba, Hyōgo]]]][[ja:]][[ja:国領水無月祭]]]][[ja:]][[Category:qq]]]][[ja:]][[en:Kokuryo Minazuki Festival]]]][[ja:]][[Category:qq]]]][[Category:qq]]]][[en:Kokuryo Minazuki Festival]]]][[Category:qq]]
